  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed advertisement would be excessive in scale representing an intrusive and unsympathetic addition to the streetscene. The proposals would have a detrimental impact on the character and appearance of the locally listed building and the Parktown Estate Conservation Area and would also impact on the setting of a Grade II listed bridge and Grade II listed railway station. The proposal fails to comply with the NPPF (2023), the NPPG (2019) and policies LP1, LP2, LP3 and LP9 of Wandsworth's Local Plan (2023).",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed advertisement may impact the safety of road users and pedestrians contrary to policies LP2 and LP9 of Wandsworth's Local Plan (2023).",
    "Reason : 3 - Notwithstanding this decision, the Applicant is advised of the need to contact TfL separately regarding a licence to install scaffolding over a public footpath. "
